Although feminism is described as “the advocacy of women’s rights on the grounds of political, social, and economic equality to men,” despite common belief, you don’t have identify as a woman to advocate for these rights.

My current partner is a great example of this; apart from his class, he is very privileged from a cultural perspective, being a straight, white, cisgender, able-bodied male. The fact that our relationship is interracial adds another complexity
